              <h2>How We Evaluate and Partner</h2>
              <p>Every investment begins with the same question: can this business become a category leader in its Sri Lankan or regional market? Our process is designed to answer that with rigour and speed.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ip-a-grid">
              <div class="ip-card"><div class="ip-step-num">01</div><h4>Sourcing &amp; Screening</h4><p>Proprietary deal flow through HNB Group's 250+ corporate banking relationships and the HNB Investment Bank M&amp;A and capital markets teams.</p><ul><li>Minimum LKR 150Mn revenue</li><li>Clear path to LKR 1Bn+ at exit</li><li>Management with provable track record</li><li>Structural competitive advantage</li></ul></div>
              <div class="ip-card"><div class="ip-step-num">02</div><h4>Diligence</h4><p>8–12 week diligence process. Financial, legal, commercial, and technical due diligence conducted with panel advisors. Management reference checks across 10+ touchpoints.</p><ul><li>3-year audited financials minimum</li><li>Market sizing (bottom-up and top-down)</li><li>Regulatory and ESG screening</li><li>Technology and IP assessment</li></ul></div>
              <div class="ip-card"><div class="ip-step-num">03</div><h4>Structuring</h4><p>Preference for minority equity with board seat and information rights. Convertible instruments and revenue-linked notes used where full equity is structurally complex.</p><ul><li>Ticket size: LKR 200Mn–LKR 800Mn</li><li>Holding period: 5–10 years</li><li>Board representation standard</li><li>No leverage at LVL fund level</li></ul></div>
              <div class="ip-card"><div class="ip-step-num">04</div><h4>Value Creation</h4><p>Active ownership through a 100-day onboarding plan, quarterly business reviews, and an in-house operating partner programme.</p><ul><li>Strategic planning facilitation</li><li>HNB Group network access</li><li>Talent and governance advisory</li><li>Export market introductions</li></ul></div>
              <div class="ip-card"><div class="ip-step-num">05</div><h4>Exit Planning</h4><p>Exit pathways prepared from Day 1. Options include CSE IPO (leveraging HNB Stockbrokers relationship), strategic trade sale, or management buyout with HNB financing support.</p><ul><li>CSE IPO pipeline coordination</li><li>Strategic buyer outreach (M&amp;A)</li><li>Secondary block trade capability</li><li>MBO financing through HNB network</li></ul></div>
              <div class="ip-card"><div class="ip-step-num">06</div><h4>Investor Reporting</h4><p>As a listed company, LVL publishes quarterly NAV updates, annual reports, and ad-hoc disclosures per CSE Listing Rules.</p><ul><li>Quarterly NAV announcements</li><li>Annual report + AGM</li><li>CSE regulatory disclosures</li><li>Institutional investor briefings</li></ul></div>
