              <p>Discipline at each stage is what separates a good investment from a great one. We move at the pace of conviction, not calendar.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ip-flow">
              <div class="ip-step"><div class="ip-step-circle">01</div><h4>Screen</h4><p>Initial 2-page screening against mandate criteria. Decision in 5 business days.</p></div>
              <div class="ip-step"><div class="ip-step-circle">02</div><h4>Diligence</h4><p>8–12 weeks. Financial, legal, commercial, technical and ESG review.</p></div>
              <div class="ip-step"><div class="ip-step-circle">03</div><h4>IC Approval</h4><p>Investment Committee review. Independent non-executive majority.</p></div>
              <div class="ip-step"><div class="ip-step-circle">04</div><h4>Active Ownership</h4><p>Board seat, 100-day plan, quarterly reviews. Operating partner programme.</p></div>
              <div class="ip-step"><div class="ip-step-circle">05</div><h4>Exit</h4><p>IPO, trade sale, or MBO. 5–10 year target hold; exit prepared from day one.</p></div>
            </div>
            <div class="ip-criteria">
              <div class="ip-criterion"><h5>Minimum Revenue Threshold</h5><p>LKR 150Mn annual revenue minimum ensures the business has demonstrated market fit before LVL capital is committed.</p></div>
              <div class="ip-criterion"><h5>Sector Mandate</h5><p>Energy, technology, export, healthcare, and logistics. We do not invest in real estate, consumer finance, or retail hospitality.</p></div>
              <div class="ip-criterion"><h5>Ticket Size</h5><p>LKR 200Mn to LKR 800Mn per initial investment. Follow-on reserves of up to 30% of initial ticket maintained for top performers.</p></div>
              <div class="ip-criterion"><h5>ESG Screen</h5><p>Mandatory environmental, social, and governance baseline assessment. Coal, tobacco, and arms excluded absolutely.</p></div>
              <div class="ip-criterion"><h5>Management Test</h5><p>Founder or incumbent CEO must remain actively operational post-investment. LVL does not take controlling stakes to run businesses directly.</p></div>
              <div class="ip-criterion"><h5>Exit Readiness</h5><p>At least one credible exit pathway must exist at entry — IPO-ready financials, identifiable strategic buyers, or management with buyout capacity.</p></div>
